# Table 1 Representation methods for enzyme catalysis

|Method|Description|Visualization|Ref<sup>a</sup>|
| :-: | :-: | :-: | :-: |
|**Reaction**||||
|SMILES|A specification in the form of a line notation for describing the structure.|CCO>> CC=O|<sup>40</sup>|
|Fingerprint|Vectorization of reactions using methods like symmetric difference or self-supervised learning.|[0, 0, 0, 1, …, -1]|<sup>41</sup>|
|Template|The substructures of molecules that participate in the reaction.|[C;H0:2]([OH:3])=[O:4]>>CC[O:3][C;HO:2](=[O:4])|<sup>20</sup>|
|Reaction graph|The graph representation of reactions which contains the nodes for chemical species and edges for interactions between them.|![](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>42</sup>|
|**Pathway**||||
|Tree graph|An undirected graph representing a pathway where any two nodes are connected by exactly one path.|![](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>44</sup>|
|Hypergraph|The graph representation contains hyperedges that can join multiple nodes.|![](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>45</sup>|
|Large-scale network|A network representation at macro scales, typically used for metabolic systems.|![Watts–Strogatz small-world model](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>46</sup>|
|**Enzyme**||||
|String|The systematic name of enzymes|β-D-glucose, oxygen 1-oxidoreductase|<sup>22</sup>|
|Sequence|The amino acid sequence|MKDCS…|<sup>33</sup>|
|EC number|A numerical classification system for enzymes|EC 1.1.1.1|<sup>33</sup>|
|PSSM|A scoring matrix providing amino acid substitution scores for each position|![](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>66</sup>|
|Topological representation|A description of amino acids based on the atomic connection index|-|<sup>49</sup>|
|Distance map|A two-dimensional matrix representing residue–residue distances|![](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>48</sup>|
|Geometric representation|Including position of atoms, protein shape, and size|![](data:image/png;base64,)|<sup>49</sup>|

<sup>a</sup>The selected reference is a classic example of using or describing the corresponding representation.
